#: ../../shared_folder.rst:23
msgid "Access privileges"
msgstr ""

#: ../../shared_folder.rst:25
msgid ""
"A shared folder is always owned by a group of users (:guilabel:`Owning "
"group`). Each member of the group is allowed to read the folder contents. "
"Optionally the group can be entitled to modify the folder contents and the "
"read permission can be extended to everyone accessing the system.  This "
"simple permission model is based on the traditional UNIX file system "
"permissions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shared_folder.rst:32
msgid ""
"Access privileges can be refined further with the :guilabel:`ACL` tab, "
"allowing individual users and other groups to gain read and write "
"permissions.  This extended permission model is based on the POSIX ACL "
"specification."
msgstr ""

